<edge source="Splunk Enterprise 10.0.2" target="Splunk Enterprise 9.3.8">
  <data key="d7">26.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Splunk Enterprise 10.0.2 represents an upgraded version of the software compared to Splunk Enterprise 9.3.8, which is currently considered outdated by security standards. System administrators are strongly advised to adopt Splunk Enterprise 10.0.2 due to its enhanced security features and improved functionality. The upgrade addresses detected vulnerabilities in version 9.3.8, resolves existing performance issues, and introduces significant improvements in both security measures and system performance.

The recommendation for upgrading from version 9.3.8 to the latest version is based on recent findings of security weaknesses in the current software. Upgrading ensures that the system remains protected against potential threats and operates more efficiently, thereby providing a better user experience with added stability and reliability. The update not only mitigates identified weaknesses but also offers substantial enhancements in terms of overall security and performance.

All descriptions consistently recommend moving from Splunk Enterprise 9.3.8 to version 10.0.2 due to improved security measures and additional features, emphasizing the need for a secure and efficient system environment. Upgrading from 9.3.8 to 10.0.2 is recommended due to detected weaknesses in the current version and improvements in the newer version, addressing recent security vulnerabilities and optimizing system performance. The upgrade includes important security enhancements and addresses identified weaknesses, ensuring that users benefit from the latest advancements in both security and performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Recommendation for upgrading from version 9.3.8 to 10.0.2 due to identified weaknesses.&lt;SEP&gt;Users are encouraged to move from version 9.3.8 to the newer version 10.0.2 due to recent security updates.&lt;SEP&gt;There is a clear upgrade path from Splunk Enterprise 9.3.8 to the newer version 10.0.2.&lt;SEP&gt;The recommendation is made to upgrade from Splunk Enterprise 9.3.8 to the latest version, Splunk Enterprise 10.0.2.</data>
  <data key="d9">improvement,recommendation,security enhancement,security improvement,security update,software update,software upgrade,update,upgrade,upgrade path,upgrade recommendation,upgrade suggestion,version change,version improvement,version progression,version update,version upgrade,vulnerability patching</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-07959bdb8bab221c9c80a1c3e85776b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-490df5a6810de4f040c4fe2681e6ed6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f1e5469f6278ea8a34bff96b293b69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0add79f46581b83deba682a2c89cdb7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d3d3acb3c191c9e65fac21b5ed9284f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7504d68fad10caa1cd0ea41314ed2ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5096c0cdf6972a3670732e4f9be1d36a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67cc5a5ed7a1cbea5f9e6d5f5d08ab51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c4967b23b72f04d5c4ef37149d21ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-996c8aba3ce4de0e9bb90c0d569231f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0c6684aa00106f16e7869f519061642&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-738a58105cbf665748b3257e0cfee9ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0cd3e323fc2a43e461d7af757b08706&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfcf7e8f6051fb59b7f2cec85fa4dc4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-412e17859c430b9ce8b929bc152053ef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5930b403906ecb929487592cef5210f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56b76e765b58a558604d5d6f2575d2ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1364984bd10139c2ef2cd5907a3a7591&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2940790b50eb2cba2a5e944b95a94dd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ebe784b7ece61edcdd2e054763c0ce3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79f23819b8640c43571e6e9b3e4098e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5479196dee25b34d077c01190c6c728b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-75fa98905e1d68515f390e75c46adddb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25d7c29d65aa0e4d54fb4af54207fa0d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f62a98ad02d11a4c9618cbda43281859&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b9e37e8f7e8a98183b1724c16ce814a</data>
