<edge source="Splunk Enterprise 10.0.2" target="E Customer">
  <data key="d7">9.0</data>
  <data key="d8">(E Customer, Splunk Enterprise 10.0.2) refers to a recommendation for an entity known as the E customer to upgrade their current system from version 9.3.8 to the latest release, Splunk Enterprise 10.0.2. This upgrade is advised primarily due to recent vulnerabilities and weaknesses that have been identified in earlier versions of Splunk Enterprise, which could potentially compromise security. Upgrading ensures enhanced system stability, better performance, and improved security features. The recommendation aims to optimize the E customer's system for more efficient operations while addressing critical updates and security fixes implemented in version 10.0.2. Overall, transitioning from 9.3.8 to Splunk Enterprise 10.0.2 is strongly recommended to protect against potential risks and to leverage the latest advancements in system optimization and security enhancements.&lt;SEP&gt;The latest version of Splunk Enterprise, 10.0.2, is recommended for the E customer to upgrade due to security weaknesses found in their current version.</data>
  <data key="d9">future software version,future version,improved security,recommended upgrade,recommends,security enhancement,upgrade recommendation,upgrade to</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-cafeb58d25cc4cbc85eaf07cf415496a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7743e93210e95e8e40e0d2a627684b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72f381579d364fa91cc3e73153e0af97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bddb98b4a84e394c0a4558b42ae12d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-412e17859c430b9ce8b929bc152053ef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e6e1908b68b82814f06780675f7938b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-068ca517cbebf973fd4089bd45ef615c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942b136689124792272bc32a2898842c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f62a98ad02d11a4c9618cbda43281859</data>
